On 05 Aug 1999 13:23:34 -0400, "Stefan Monnier"
<monnier+lists/linux/kernel/news/@tequila.cs.yale.edu> wrote:
>info and texinfo pages should be arranged so that I can replace
>
>	man 2 open                      man 3 fclose
>with
>	info syscall open               info libc fclose
At least with glibc2 you can do this, at least if you compile and install
it yourself. Glibc2 install adds references to all functions, constants
etc. to info/dir. So I *can* do 'info fclose' and get the libc info on
fclose().
